===Expansion of scope in Ontario (2015)===
Ontario already had the highest rates relating to probate taxes, but is still faced with large [[budget deficit]]s.<ref name="Dollar2014">{{cite web |url= https://www.sunnet.sunlife.com/files/advisor/english/PDF/Changes_coming_to_Ontarios_Estate_Administration_Tax.pdf|title= Changes for Ontario’s Estate Administration Tax|last= Dollar|first= Stuart L.|date= April 2014|website= sunlife.com|publisher= Sun Life Financial}}</ref> The provincial 2011 budget speech stated that there was still a compliance problem with respect to the Estate Administration Tax,<ref name="Dollar2014"/> and it accordingly passed amending legislation that year,<ref>[https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/s11009 ''Better Tomorrow for Ontario Act (Budget Measures), 2011], S.O. 2011, c. 9, Schedule 14</ref> coming into effect on January 1, 2015,<ref>{{Cite canlaw
|link= https://www.ontario.ca/laws/regulation/140310|type= reg|regtitle= Information required under section 4.1 of the Act|regnumber= O. Reg. 310/14}}</ref> which provided for the following changes:

:* in addition to the requirement to pay a deposit on tax that was already in place in order to receive an estate certificate,{{efn|a term that covers letters probate and letters of administration}} an estate representative must file an estate information return within 90 days of the date the certificate was issued, together with any balance of tax still owing
:* where a later statement under the ''Estates Act'' discloses any property that was not previously disclosed on the estate information return, the estate representative must file an amended return within 30 days of the statement date
:* the Minister of Finance has similar powers to examine the information as he has under the ''Retail Sales Tax Act''
:* there is no procedure for the estate to receive a clearance certificate with respect to closing off any further liability<ref name="Brennan2015"/>

The changes have been viewed as "put[ting] undue pressure on executors{{em dash}}often family members{{em dash}}faced with balancing their grief with trying to make the Finance Ministry happy."<ref name="Brennan2015">{{cite news |last= Brennan|first= Richard|date= September 24, 2015|title= Ontario government wants estate tax paid sooner|url= https://www.thestar.com/news/queenspark/2015/09/24/ontario-liberal-government-wants-estate-tax-paid-sooner.html|newspaper= [[The Toronto Star]] }}</ref>

